inn1.comm: and it's well wide of off stump, Billy Bowden calls it a wide and there's no doubt about that decision
left alone outside off at 140kph, no swing there for Bond
lovely ball, that one swings in quite prodigiously and Watson goes for an off-drive, the ball sails between bat and pad
Watson's off the mark with a clip through midwicket, although it wasn't timed, he was trying to drive that straighter
an lbw appeal here, the ball swings in and hits Watson in line, but high up on his thigh and definitely would have sailed over the top
left alone outside off, Watson keen to have a bit of a look at Bond at this stage
oh, nearly got him! Movement in again from Bond, and some bounce, Watson plays off the back foot and very nearly chops it back into his off stump, the ball bounces just wide of the stumps
Haddin faces his first ball and it's off the meat of the bat, a good strong straight drive that is well fielded by Franklin at mid-on
Southee strays onto the pads, Haddin clips a single out to the right of Franklin at mid-on
straight, on off stump, Watson drives to mid-off
no swing here from Southee, just probing on off stump and Watson defends
Watson clips a single off his pads, down to fine leg
Haddin looks for a big drive through off, but can't beat the man at cover
full and wide of off at 143kph, Watson drives straight to cover, he'd be annoyed at not getting that one through the infield
drives to extra cover
clipped away to fine leg, a bit too straight from Bond
left alone outside off
quick running from Haddin, he nudges it back past the bowler and takes off immediately for a well-judged single
good line outside off, no swing though, and Watson angles the bat and defends towards gully
a bit of outswing from Southee, full and wide of off, Haddin tries for a drive but misses
on the pads, this one doesn't swing and Haddin clips a single to midwicket
lovely straight drive to the boundary, it was on the stumps and Watson looked like he was playing a simple forward defensive but timed it so well that it raced away
oops, nearly a costly mix-up, Watson wants a single to midwicket but Haddin doesn't, and Watson turns back and gets home with a dive
nudged away to off
good line on off, Watson defends
left alone outside off
good bounce here from Bond, he's working hard, and Haddin lets it go through to Hopkins
Haddin punches a drive wide of Vettori at mid-off and they get through for a single
fine fielding from Guptill at cover point, Watson tries to get a square drive through point and Guptill moves quickly across to keep it to a single
swing and a miss! Bond nibbles one away outside off, Haddin has a big windy whoosh and lucky for him it misses his edge
slower ball, defended by Haddin
a thickish edge away through the vacant third slip area and third man can't quite get across to cut it off
slower ball at 119kph, on the pads and Watson picks it, working a single to midwicket
Haddin misses again, he's looking a little scratchy, tries to guide this one wide of the slips but there's more bounce than he expected
141kph, Southee beats Haddin again, lovely bowling and Haddin's attempted drive doesn't connect
howzat? Immediate denial from Rudi Koertzen. Pitching on off and jagging back, Haddin gets hit on the flap of the pad and Hawk-Eye shows that going over the top
left alone outside off
beaten again, Watson was trying to late cut and Bond's extra bounce did him
cracking cover drive this time, Bond gets just a little too full and Watson connects with this one, finding the gap wide of short cover
no shot offered outside off
angling in to Watson, who gets forward with bat and pad close together to defend
slower ball, left alone outside off
angled bat from Watson, he guides a single to third man
another slower delivery, Watson works a single away behind square leg
good bounce again, Haddin gets under it and cuts deliberately in the air to third man, it falls safely short of the fielder
super bounce again, it really surprises Watson as he tries a late cut, Hopkins takes it at shoulder height
quick single, good running as Watson's forward defensive runs away behind the stumps and Haddin calls him through
on the stumps this time, Haddin tries to go through leg but doesn't connect properly
good line on off, Haddin defends
131kph, just a touch slower, but wide of off and Watson leaves it alone
angles in towards off stump, pushed back to mid-off
moving in to Watson again, defended to leg
and finally Watson gets one that he wants to go after, 131kph again from Bond, fullish on the stumps, and Watson lifts it high and long, over the bowler's head for six
a good-looking pull flies off the bat but straight to Ingram at deep midwicket
on the hips, clipped away to midwicket
Haddin tries to go on the attack, backing off and driving hard but straight to mid-off
Haddin gets hold of this one, advances and waits on a slightly slower ball before launching it over mid-on for a boundary
that's a wild swing! Shorter and wider of off, Haddin threw the kitchen sink at that but it beats the bat
nudged to leg for no run
another boundary from Haddin, easy as you like he gives himself a little room and guides it over mid-off
yorker, hits Haddin's foot as he backs away towards leg
great shot! Just short enough and Watson pulls viciously through midwicket
angled away to third man
Haddin tries for the drive down the ground again, but doesn't get hold of it and Vettori at mid-off gets across and knocks it down
beaten, Watson tries to guide that wide of the keeper
Watson goes for the cut and again Franklin beats the bat
on the pads, Watson works it to backward square leg and can't get a run
well-timed cover drive, but not so well-placed as it finds the fielder in the circle
another one flies off the bat, they do get a single this time as the man at point knocks it down
133kph, left alone outside off
Watson drives, there's a man at long-off now so it's just a single
wonderful fielding from Brendon McCullum at short cover, he hurls himself to his right and stops Haddin's big drive

what a great shot! Outstanding strike from Haddin as he walks a couple of paces down the pitch and lifts this one from off stump over wide midwicket, he's got under it well enough to cover the full distance
short and four. Poor ball, Franklin shouldn't be sending down leg-side bouncers at 129kph and Watson pulls it through square, easy as you like
tries to dab that one wide of the keeper but can't connect
driven uppishly towards mid-off, the man moves across to keep it to a single
Haddin has decided his area is down the ground so he goes again, getting under it but doesn't quite time it and the ball lobs inside the boundary and is cut off by the man at long-on
crunched to point and Guptill makes another good stop, that one was travelling
slower ball, nudged away to point
tight call there from Rudi Koertzen, Watson tries to lash Tuffey through point but misses and it is pretty much on the line that guides the umpires regarding wides
nudged towards leg
bad ball, on the hips and with fine leg up, Watson has no problem guiding that one away to the boundary
wide again, could have been called had Watson not found the middle of the bat, he's down on one knee to drive over cover, lovely stroke
gone! Watson tries to go over midwicket but he hasn't timed that well enough. There's a man on the boundary, it's Martin Guptill, and he takes a safe catch.
nice deft placement from Haddin, he waits on this and guides it behind point, Bond running around from third man makes a diving save, impressive commitment for a 34-year-old
Ponting's first ball is left alone outside off
drifts in and Haddin drives a single to long-on
tossed up on off, no real spin there and Ponting defends
just a hint of curve in, Ponting drives through cover
drifting in towards the leg stump, Haddin cautiously knocks another single to long-on
oh Ricky, what was that? So much for getting his eye in, Ponting tries for a big slog over midwicket but gets a thick top edge that flies high and is taken by Brendon McCullum at cover
driven towards mid-off
a shout for Clarke first ball, Tuffey wanted the lbw but it was angled in and looked to be heading down leg side
Clarke is forward this time to defend
pushed away defensively
slower ball, Clarke pushes to mid-on
driven back down the pitch and Tuffey gets down quickly to make the save, keeps Clarke on strike and doesn't let him get off the mark
nudged away to point to end a good over from Tuffey
left alone outside off, no spin there
drifting in, Haddin defends
punched away through point and the man in the deep collects
not much turn again, Clarke defends
pushed away to off
on the back foot, Clarke gets a single through point
Clarke clips it into his pads, thinks about a quick single but doesn't go for it
on the hip, Clarke works it away behind square leg
pushed away through cover
bat onto pad once again, and again there's no single there
oh well played! Tuffey drops in short and well wide of off, somehow Clarke pulls it from out there down into the ground and through midwicket for a boundary, a really good shot
forward to defend this time
and Vettori goes for a maximum! Haddin uses his feet and launches Vettori back over his head for six, that really did look effortless
clipped away to mid-on
curving in to off stump, Clarke defends
drifts in again, worked through midwicket
another one from Haddin, this time over long-on as he takes a couple of steps down the pitch, gets under it and thumps it down the ground
pushed away to the off side
on the stumps immediately, clipped to midwicket
Haddin mixes it up by just opening the face of the bat and guiding this to the vacant third man area, Broom runs back from in the circle and collects it
flicked to leg and Guptill is super quick, dives across from midwicket to make a save

what impressive timing, Haddin drives in the air down the ground, and timed so well that Tuffey at long-on can't get across despite it being only a few metres from him. And that's the fifty for Haddin.
pushed away to leg
good timing again, driven along the ground back past the bowler, this time Tuffey is fast enough to cut it off
ooh, almost a caught and bowled, Haddin looks for the big drive and checks his shot, it bounces just short of Vettori
guided to gully, can't beat the field
punched away to long-off for a single
wider of off, Clarke slashes at that without much footwork and finds the man at backward point
Clarke skips down the pitch this time and drives back past the bowler
curving in nicely, no real spin though and driven back to the bowler
Styris is on target and Clarke drives to long-on
113kph, Haddin drives straight to McCullum at cover
strays down leg, no doubt about that one being called wide
straight-bat defence from Haddin, that one was just outside off
130kph, a bit quicker and it's pushed back to the bowler
opens the face but just finds the man at short third man
on the back foot, Haddin drives to mid-on
Clarke looks to crunch that through cover but mistimes it
drifting in from around the wicket, driven down towards mid-on

what a catch! Magnificent return take from Vettori! Haddin has positively laced that drive after taking a couple of steps down the pitch, it flew wide of Vettori but he thrust his left hand out and somehow it stuck. That ball was seriously well struck, great stuff from Vettori.
White is forward to defend his first ball
pushed away down towards long-off and White is off the mark
tossed up and it's cut away forward of point for a single
drives to mid off
edges on the bounce to slip, good save there
plays and misses at a good one outside off
short and Clarke tries to pull, with both feet off the ground the ball lobbing to mid on for a simple catch
leaves outside off, goodish pace at 148 kph
short outside off, just inside the line so it's not a wide
leaves one go outside off
gets well forward in defence, playing it to cover point
defends towards the off side again
forces off the back foot out to deep cover point
forces off the back foot to mid off
comes forward in defence, another very tidy over NZ bowlers doing an excellent job here at the moment
defends to cover point
defends off the back foot, Bond appears to be a little bit extra into that ball
short of a length again, defends to point
defends again off the back foot
digs a very ball out towards deep extra cover, a single taken
defends off the back foot to cover point
clips a ball to mid wicket
pushes gently to deep mid on, easy single taken
drives to cover
well flighted and  drives it to long on
drives to cover point
pushes forward and is beaten between bat and pad, the keeper  Hopkins whips the bails off and the TV replay is called for
drives to mid off, finds the fielder there
defends off the back foot to mid off, sharpish pace again at 148kph
leg side, worked off the pads and heads for long leg, Tuffey down there makes a mess of it and they come back for an extra run
short outside off, Rudi Koertzen says it's a wide and on replay it looks a poor call
short, Hussey is surprised by the speed and bounce but manages to get it to ground
drives off the inside half of the bat towards mid off
drives to short cover and Brendan McCullum dives to his left and performs a brilliant piece of fielding..........not bad by a keeper without the  gloves on!!!
driving to deep mid on, nicely played
well flighted and White drives it to long off
works off the pads to deep mid wicket
plays off the back foot to cover point
shorter, forces off the back foot to the cover point sweeper
outside off and neatly cut out to deep point
forces off the back foot to long off
back of a length and defends to the on side
moves slightly to the off side, working the ball to long leg. Smart batting
goes to the leg side this time and it's aimed at his pads - worked to long leg for just a single this time
forces off the back foot to cover point
drives to mid off, single taken
drives wide of mid off and it runs away to the fence, great placement there dissecting mid off and cover with precision
worked to mid wicket
pushes to point, finds the fielder
drives to mid off, good bowling this since giving up the boundary first ball
worked to a gap at square leg
drives past the short cover and an easy single to long off
played to long on, easy single
drives to long off, another pretty easy single
drives to  long off, another handy single for Australia
short, pulls with little effort to deep square leg
works off his pads to deep square leg, Franklin does well to keep it to a single
punches off the back foot to long off
works out to deep square leg
drives towards mid on, Vettori gets across and saves it with his foot
drives out to deep cover, plenty of force in that shot
works to the leg side, finds the gap
outside off and carved out to deep cover point, raising the 150 for the Aussies
forces off the back foot to cover point, ending Vettori's spell
full and hammers a drive back past the bowlers left hand, excellent timing
plays defensively to point
forces off the back foot to cover point
aims to drive to mid off, plays it a bit early and it ends up at mid on
forces off the back foot out to deep cover point
drops it into the off side, Guptill charges in from point and underarms the ball into the stumps - home safely enough, no referral called for
defends off the back foot to backward point and Broom charges in and fields preventing a single
straighter ball, worked to mid wicket finding the fielder
drives to cover and Guptill does well moving to his left
works to deep square leg, finds a gap that allows them to grab a couple
short and tries to hook, a big shout for caught behind perhaps to con the umpire into not calling a wide, which Bowden does eventually call
plays back in defence
defends to point, time for some drinks at Eden Park with 15 overs left in the Aussie innings
driven to long off for an easy single
works a leg side ball backward of square leg and it rolls past Bond going away for a boundary
advances and drives to long off
short, pulls over mid wicket - only just as Guptill jumped high into the air and couldn't quite get a hand on it
short and hooked it away flat and somehow for six! Good shot but I'd doubt if that would be six at any other venue in the world
comes forward and defends to the bowler
straightish, drives towards the onside
drives off a thick inside edge to deep square leg
works off his pads to mid wicket
drives out to deep cover point
slower ball, short and pulls to deep square leg for another four
short down leg side, obvious wide
struck on the pad -- well outside off
defends towards cover
drives into a gap at extra cover
slower ball, plays to the bowler
drives to long off, another easy single
moves to leg, the ball follows him and he punches it to mid wicket
drives to mid  on, finding the fielder
cuts a short ball to deep cover point
drives  to mid off
punches a drive to long off
slower ball yorker which he drives into the off side
chips a drive to long on
drives to long off, another very tidy over there just 4 runs from it
makes room to leg and drives to deep mid off
drives past Guptill at cover for a single
drives to long on another easy single, good tight bowling here though with nothing too short
shortish, pulls to deep square leg
makes room to leg and drives to long off
drives square of wicket, beating the diving point fielder - crashing into the boundary
drives hard to cover, finding the fielder there
drives straight, Bond comes in from long off but can't prevent the two being taken
drives out to deep cover point
leg side, clipped in the air to deep square leg, Southee keeps it to a single
drives to long on - bringing up the 200
drives to cover, fielded by Guptill on the 30 yard circle
advances and drives to long off
moves to leg, pushes back to the bowler and Tuffey has a ping at the stumps - no contact
drives back to the bowler who fumbles a regulation stop, no penalty for that luckily
drives to long off, another easy single
works a low full toss to wide long on
pushes into a gap at cover point
he opens up his front leg and slogs it out to deep mid wicket - just beating the fielder
he goes again, slogging another one over mid wicket for back to back sixes!!
he goes for three in a row, but doesn't get hold of it, Brendan McCullum holds on to the change running in from deep mid on
short, tries to pull but gets an under edge into his pad
drives to long off, easy single
defends a 113kph delivery back up the pitch
full toss, drives to long off, Guptill fields there
drives to long on, a fairly full ball which he couldn't do a lot else with
drives to long off
drives back past the bowler to the deep
digs out a yorker to long off
slashes and misses a slower ball outside off, pretty good over there from Tuffey
a low full toss that is driven hard to long off, 50 up for Hussey from 61 balls - a good knock
clips out to deep square leg, good running nets them two runs
full, Hopes was looking to play a flip shot but in the end outsmarted himself and pushed it into the off side
full and wide, square drives with power through point
drives wide of mid on and McCullum  is outstanding again making a diving save on the rope
full and digs it out to the bowler
full and smashed over mid wicket into the construction site, cracking shot
full and drives in the air hard to Nathan McCullum at long on who falls forward and holds a good catch
flashes at one outside off and misses
cracks a slower ball out to deep cover point
chips a full ball to mid wicket and Tuffey sticks his left hand up and made a great attempt to catch it, but couldn't hang on
pushes into the off side, end of an interesting over
full and gets it away to short fine leg
clips of the pads to deep mid wicket
makes room to leg and drives to long on
full, driven to long on, just a single
full and chips to deep mid wicket, good bowling once again
drives to long on for another single
drives hard to long on, another single
drives hard and gets an edge through the slip area to a fine 3rd man
flashes and misses outside off,
works to a gap at mid wicket
slogs to deep mid wicket and Broom runs in off the rope and it just falls short of him, however he may been a bit late in picking it up
swings a misses outside off
drives back at the bowler, it hits the stumps at the bowlers end
swings hard at a full ball, driving to long on
chips to deep square leg, again very full and hard to slog it away
reverse sweeps to 3rd man, flying off the bat to the boundary
chips a very full ball to mid wicket
advances and drives to deep mid off, actually made it into a yorker
makes room and drives hard through the covers - slightly slower ball there
knee high full toss, drives in the air to long on
straight driven past the bowler, Guptill does well on the rope at straight hit and saves the boundary
full and wide, drives to long off where Guptill features once again
makes room to leg and glances to short fine leg, just the single, a yard or two either side of the fielder and is was a boundary
swings hard and misses, Hopkins fumbles, Hopes takes off and the keeper regathers and fires it to Tuffey who runs out Hopes - that's the innings

inn2.comm: leaves alone outside off - 137 kph
full and drives with great power to the cover point boundary much to the delight of 13,500 people in
slashes at one outside off and misses
leaves this one outside off
defends off the back foot to point
square drives a full ball over backward point into the old terracing at Eden Park, great start for the Kiwis in this run chase
drives hard to cover, good looking shot first up
middle and leg, tries to work to leg but it ends up at mid on
swings and misses at one outside off
whips it off the pads to the deep in the leg side
hit on the pad as he tries to work to leg, a good shout from the bowler who let that rip at 144kph
gets one that jags into him, he takes the bottom hand off the bat in a back foot defensive shot
thrashes at one outside off and misses, kept a bit low on the way to the keeper
defends to the  off side
works into a gap at mid wicket for a single
short and pulls it away through forward square leg - cracking shot
goes back in defence to a good length ball
short and hooks it in the deep square leg construction site - McCullum seeing them very well early
slightly slower ball, tries to turn to leg getting an inside edge onto his pad
plays to mid on
played defensive - but it's a no ball, so we'll have a free hit
short, leg side bumper which follows the batsman as he moves to leg
plays back in defence to the bowler
defends to the on-side
drives towards mid on
plays and misses to one outside off, not a bad start for Johnson silencing the crowd
makes room and charges at the bowler, swinging and missing outside off
full and wide, he cracks a powerful drive through the covers to the boundary
defends to mid off
tries to work to leg, getting an edge and Haddin dives to his right, in front of slip and hangs onto a blinder of a catch. The end of a brief but entertaining innings
drives a full ball to cover point
tries to pull and it hit high on the pad
worked off the stumps to mid wicket
lofts over forward square leg, very wristy shot timed superbly
ducks a bouncer that swing late after it passes the batsman
plays a leg side ball to long leg
plays off the back foot towards mid on
drives and edges a full ball to 3rd man, Harris dives and saves it on the line - clever fielding
leaves a short ball outside off
full and wide and it powered through the covers in fine style
defends off the back foot towards cover
defends off the back foot back to the bowler
defends into the covers
turns an off-side ball through forward of square leg
clips off the pads fine, past the fielder who is up inside the circle, a poor ball which got what it deserved
flips off the pads to short fine leg, finding Johnson this time
tries to turn to leg and is hit on the pad and Umpire Koertzen has given him - looked a bit leg side to me
an appeal first up and he is gone - caught on the crease at this one looked pretty good - dead line, height not an issue
an anti-climax, leaves it alone outside off
drives nicely to extra cover - well fielded there by Clarke
goes back and tries to turn to leg, striking him on the pad
pushes at one outside off, an appeal for a catch behind but Haddin didn't appeal
leaves outside off
leaves outside off, nearly a wide
defends into the off side
pushes to mid wicket, a reminder that Franklin is using a runner  today
defends to backward point
defends off the back foot
drives to extra cover, Clarke does the fielding
works off the back foot to a gap at square leg
plays off the back foot to 3rd man, Bollinger slides and saves down there
tries to pull and he gets a glove down the leg side, Franklin walks and he is gone -- Kiwis in all sorts of bother as Franklin limps off
he does drop short, and Styris ducks, it beats Haddin and they get five wides!!!
plays off the back foot to point
on the hip and it is worked to the short boundary at long leg, "Hot Spot" shows it actually took the glove
plays back in defence to the off side
full and wide and it gracefully thumped through the covers - right out of the meat of the bat
defends off the back foot to mid off
drives hard to Clarke at cover
full and wide, square driven to point
full and driven with great power back over the bowlers head into the advertising hoarding, ripper of  a shot
drives through the covers
defends off the back foot to cover point
drives out to deep cover point
digs out a wide ball to 3rd man
defends into the offside
plays back in defence towards cover point
wide of the batsman and swinging further away
drives to mid off, firmly struck but finds the fielder
aims a big drive and misses outside off
comes forward to one that  comes back into him slightly, good ball to end the over
drives off the back foot to point
wide and thrashes it behind point for a boundary, top shot from a widish ball
worked off the pads behind square leg
comes forward in defence to cover
wide again, slashes at it outside off and misses
full and it is smashed through mid off, hit with immense power even if it there was minimal footwork
defends off the back foot towards mid off
drives out to deep cover point
short and forces to point, Ponting there saves
plays  forward and defends to the bowler
forces off the back foot into a gap at cover point
flicks off the pads to deep square leg
turns off the stumps to backward square leg
gets a thick inside edge behind square leg to turn the strike over
tries to turn to leg, hit on the pad but well and truly missing leg stump
short and hammers a pull shot behind square leg as the rain stars to come down again
defends to point as we have a sun shower here
forces off the back foot to Ponting at cover point and they take a sharp single
defends off the back foot to mid wicket
drives to Ponting at point, they try for a single, Ponting aims and misses at the bowler's end, had he hit Styris was half a pitch short of his ground
plays back to one that moves away slightly, the edge is found and taken by Haddin - Guptil goneski!!!
drives confidently to deep cover point, nice way to get underway
clips off the toes to deep square leg
defends off the back foot to mid on
drives to cover
comes forward in defence
drives and gets an inside edge, Johnson dives and saves it at short fine leg saving maybe three runs
drives out to deep cover point
nicely driven to long off
plays back to one which appears to cut back a bit, Haddin dives to his left and takes it, there is an appeal which is answered in the negative
works off about middle peg to deep square leg
drives to deep cover point, easy single for the NZ 'keeper
defends off the back foot to short mid wicket
defends off the back foot to the bowler
short and leg side, tries to pull missing it and gets a wide
drives it with power to long on
guides a good length ball behind point to the bounhdary, played with a vey straight bat, top stroke to bring up the 100 for the homeside
comes forward and plays to backward point
drives back past the bowler towards long on
plays to backward point
comes forward in defence to play the ball to cover
comes forward and pushes a drive to deep cover point
plays back and gets an inside edge to mid wicket - time for a single
chips a ball to mid wicket
drives to long on, easy single
drives off the back foot into a gap at cover  point
aims to cut and there is an appeal for caught behind, a big shout and it appeared to be a big edge and noise - but Billy Bowden says "No"
drives to long off
drives to the bowler who fields well
plays off the back foot to mid wicket
drives to cover point, finding the gap there
plays off the back foot out to deep cover point
comes forward and deftly works it  to long on
defends to mid wicket
gets one that jags back, he inside edges into his body
drives to cover
plays to deep mid wicket for another single
comes forward and pushes it into a gap at point
outside off, drives square of the wicket
a bit of bounce and turn, played off the back foot to point
plays off the back foot to mid wicket
plays off the back foot to Ponting at point, who has a rare misfield
played to mid wicket, Hussey fields well preventing a run
leg side, played to short fine leg and Johnson saves but has a unneccessary throw and misses, conceding an overthrow
plays to Clarke at cover
drives a very full ball down to long on
plays back and slightly across one, hit on the pad but umpire Koertzen feels it was missing despite a whole hearted appeal from the bowler
advances and drives to long on
comes forward in defence towards cover
comes forward and pushes the ball to deep cover point
plays off the back foot to mid wicket
wide, tries to late cut and misses
drives to long on
plays to mid wicket, Hussey dives and can't gather, they scramble back for a couple
forces off the back foot to cover
plays off the back foot to long off
slashes at one outside and it flies away behind point for a much needed boundary
works a ball on middle stump to deep square leg, thought of two but not on this time
short and pulls to deep square leg, Harris saves on the rope and it is time for a drinks break
comes forward and defends to mid wicket

same shot as the previous ball, but this time he hits it in the air and Ponting leaps up and takes a good catch - a vital wicket and the Kiwis chances take a bit of a dive with the loss of the hero of the first ODI
comes forward and defends to the bowler
well flighted and it is driven to mid off
slog sweeps over mid wicket, good aggressive shot
comes forward in defence
defends off the back foot to point
short, pulls over square leg for a couple
plays off the back foot to cover point
goes well across to the off side and tries to glance, getting an edge onto his pads to long leg - did well to get away with that as he nearly glanced it onto his stumps
plays off the back foot to mid wicket
drives to long on to keep the strike for the next over
plays to deep mid wicket, easy single
plays off the back foot to deep square leg
drives on the bounce to cover
has a big swing at a well flighted ball, quite a good deal slower
pushes to square leg, finding the gap
leg side and clipped off the pads, Bollinger does well on the rope saving a couple of runs
short and pulls it just over the head of the fielder at mid wicket
punches a drive to deep mid on
drives to long on, nicely played to the fielder in the deep
plays across one, getting a little edge onto his pad - the ball running away to the off side
shortish, pulls to deep square leg
drives out to deep point - 114 more needed from 15 overs
drives to long on for an easy single
lofts over the bowlers head, beating Watson at long off who came around in a vain attempt to stop it
advances and lofts it over mid wicket, hit it flat and hard into the crowd - good attacking batting this
sweeps to short fine leg and yells "No", Hopkins was well on his way and Vettori runs, Hopes throws and Hauritz whips them off at the bowlers end but he is well home
goes back and across, pushing into a gap at mid wicket
played off the back foot to mid wicket - great over for the Kiwis
not the best of starts, a leg side wide
plays off the back foot to point
square drives to deep 3rd man
leg side wide as Vettori slightly distracts him by moving the off side
worked off the pads to deep square leg
drives to mid off, finding Michael Clarke
drives off the edge, beating Watson who ran around from 3rd man
defends the last ball of a long over to cover
tries to work to leg, getting a bit of pad on it
drives to backward point, fielded there by Ponting
plays off the back foot to point

bumper, hooks at it getting a top to long leg where Bollinger holds onto a catch. Might have been a fraction high for the shot, but when you need 8 an over to win you need to score off those deliveries
drives back past the bowler down to long on
pushes forward and drives to mid off
defends into the off side
defends off the back foot to mid wicket
works a length ball behind square leg
moves to the off side and works to the deep square leg boundary - risky shot, he's got a tremendous eye and gets it away to the fence
drives to long off
comes forward and defends to the bowler
tries to work to leg and gets a bit of bat onto it
shortish, pulls a quicker ball to deep backward square leg
plays a length ball that turns a fraction to deep mid wicket
slog sweeps along the ground to deep mid wicket
leg side, clips off the back foot to deep square leg
short, late cuts with power to the boundary, fantastic shot from Tuffey there - very smart batting
steps again to the off side and leg glances it
worked to deep square leg, again moving to the off side to get into the right position
swings hard at a full ball and gets an inside edge past leg stump and the' keeper to the boundary
chips a ball behind square leg for four more to the short boundary
comes forward and gets an inside edge to mid wicket, Hussey dives but can't field the ball cleanly
drives in the air behind point and it flies away for another four - the Kiwis  are right in this, making the most of the short boundary in that over
swing and misses at a wide half volley
edges towards slip, White knocks it down and they scramble a couple
comes forward and defends to cover point, another single 54 off 51 needed for the Kiwis
moves to the off side and plays it to deep square leg, hard to bowl at - mind you a yorker on middle stump might sort that out...................
defends off the back foot to mid off, "No" is the call as Clarke  was onto it like a panther
drives at a wide one and it's edge to White at slip - he's gone
gets across the crease and leg glances to the vacant long leg boundary
drives back past the bowler to long off
defends off the back foot to cover
defends off the back foot to the bowler
comes forward and defends to point
drives with some style out to deep cover point to keep the bowling
plays forward and drives at a 149kph ball and misses
tries to drive at a yorker that is wide of the off stump
down leg side, tries to work it to long leg and misses - wide given
swings and misses outside off
wide outside off, just inside the guide line that helps the umpire
works off the pads and it flies away behind square leg, Bollinger does his best on the boundary but can't stop it
drives at another very wide ball and misses outside off - again just inside the guideline for the wide call
drives over the bowlers head and that brings up a wonderful 50 off just 34 balls, what a knock!
moves to the off side and pushes to mid wicket, Clarke has a ping at the bowlers end and misses
moves to leg this time, slashes and misses
moves to leg and lofts a ball to deep square leg, landing on the first bounce to Watson
drives with some power to deep cover point
moves to the off side and works it to deep square leg, thus keeping the strike - sensible stuff
short outside off and he cuts it over the head of Bollinger at 3rd man - great shot and smart play trying to score at the shorter parts of the ground
full and leg side, a shocker of a ball and another run for NZ
cuts to 3rd man again, this time along the ground for a single
very full and he plays inside it and he loses his stump -- well bowled by Johnson, at last a bowler goes full and straight and it has paid off
flashes at a wide ball outside off and misses it
defends off the back foot back to the bowler
works to long leg - so Southee will have the strike
comes forward in defence, fielded by the bowler
plays back and is beaten outside off - good bowling
has a wild swing at a good length ball and gets an edge to 3rd man, bit of panic in that shot - but got away with it
moves to leg and tries to hit a yorker, no contact
another yorker, he makes room but misses again
full again, he digs it out behind the stumps to keep the strike - ending an excellent over for the Aussies
makes room and drives a low full toss on middle stump through cover point, unbelievable shot!!!!
backs away to leg again and lofts it over mid off.......just and it runs away for another four!!!! Great stuff from the skipper!
moves to the off side and tries to flick a length ball that goes over the top of middle................gee that was close
makes room and hammers a drive to mid off, no chance of a run as he hit it far too well
late inswinger, hits him on the pad but angling down leg
edges on the bounce just short of slip, Haddin dives tries to catch it, White knocks it down and a single is scored
drives at a wide length ball, edging to 3rd man, did well there the lad. Now Vettori on strike with 13 off 11 balls required
steps to the off side and he tries to glance it, but misses and loses his off stump - Australia wins the game and levels the series at one apiece
